    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In some places in the manual where Zend_Filter_Inflector is explained. There are pieces of example code tha tlook like this.</p>

<p><a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.layout.advanced.html#zend.layout.advanced.inflector">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>$inflector-&gt;setRules(array(
    ':script' =&gt; array('CamelCaseToUnderscore'),
    'suffix' =&gt; 'phtml'
));</p>

<p>This however triggers an error :</p>

<p>Zend_Loader_PluginLoader_Exception: Plugin by name CamelCaseToUnderscore was not found in the registry. in Zend\Loader\PluginLoader.php on line 370</p>

<p>Because the Filter 'CamelCaseToUnderscore is not present in the root of the Filter directory. It's inside a sub folder 'Word'. Prefixing CamelCaseToUnderscore with Word_ fixes this.</p>

